Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.49,0:01:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the lectures with the same realization, the same statement about reality. Can you still hear me?\NAll right. Certain spiritual information in and of itself is transformational. To have merely
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.32,0:01:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,heard it already leaps one ahead in one's understanding of reality. And so I always\Nstart with something to help us jump the whole level of the 400s, which is such a big block to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.26,0:01:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the average spiritual seeker. So we begin with the observation that nothing is causing anything.\NThe theory of causation calibrates around 460. It's central to the scientific paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.23,0:02:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's central to the Newtonian paradigm of reality. But enlightenment doesn't happen in\Nthe Newtonian paradigm of reality. It happens when you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.18,0:02:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens when you transcend it. I do have a bad throat, don't I?\NWe call 9-11 and they're sending somebody. They'll be here in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.56,0:02:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything. Everything is what it is of its own self, of its own self.\NBecause each thing is coming out of creation at this moment, being what? It's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.12,0:03:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,full of\NIt's fulfilling.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.62,0:03:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fulfilling its karmic potentiality.\NThe only question that's raised here today is do I know anything about reality
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.84,0:03:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,all along the history of God's creation?\NJust to build your own reflection from the movies of education,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.15,0:03:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,even might be a Spritzer programme,\NYou know I have pressure on my memory around my head and voice as much as I can,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.00,0:03:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It consists of not only years in a up and down process,\Nbut it also consists of ten years with the transcendent of it everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.68,0:03:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to become a rose.\NAnd if the conditions are appropriate,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it fulfills its potentiality.\NSo this petal is not causing this petal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.52,0:03:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This stem is not causing the flower.\NThe roots are not causing, nothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.87,0:03:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we witness is everything fulfilling its destiny,\Nits karmic potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.16,0:03:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to the best that it can under prevailing conditions.\NConsequently, evolution and creation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.21,0:04:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,are one and the same thing.\NWhat we witness is the unfolding of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.41,0:04:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,from instant to instant.\NIsn't that simple?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.17,0:04:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason it's critical is,\Nthe other reason it's critical to know this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.56,0:04:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is because if you reverence the concept of causality,\Nwhat you establish then is there must be an I causing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.01,0:04:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be,\Nyou create the duality of a personal separate I
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.63,0:04:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,from the infinite reality of the presence of divinity.\NConsequently, causality firmly then establishes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:05:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a duality in your mind.\NPeople who are somewhat naive will remark
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.19,0:05:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that the doctor is channeling something.\NYou know, he does great channeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.56,0:05:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That comes from that same idea of duality.\NYou see, channeling is in duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.95,0:05:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There would be an entity on the other side\Nlike whispering in my ear,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.80,0:05:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there's a me that hears that\Nand announces it to you, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.37,0:05:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That would really freak me out.\NDave, come on, listen, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.67,0:05:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhen you see reality, you see then
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.18,0:05:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that everything is merely being what it is.\NSo the speaker at this moment is spontaneously being
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.54,0:06:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is, speaking for the knowingness within,\Nwhich is a presence which is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.30,0:06:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I can ask questions all day, I don't hear anything.\NSo each thing stands forth to the fullest extent
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.02,0:06:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that it can be what it is at that moment.\NWe may see it as limitation, but that's our perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.57,0:06:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's being as good as it can be at the moment.\NEven though we would say it's being bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.99,0:06:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You take the package and you can't open it,\Nyou get angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.75,0:06:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are now packaged to make sure\Nyou can't get them open.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.87,0:06:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way to get them open.\NI struggle, I try.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.62,0:07:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So each thing is being what it can be\Nto the greatest extent it can be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.69,0:07:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to calibrate something.\NWhat I'm holding in mind is 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.04,0:07:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,505, 506, 508. My god, that's some dog. We ran into a wonderful loving dog in the\Ncorner there who looked up at me and says, I'm over 500. Turned out he's 505.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.56,0:07:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually a dog's wagging tail is right at 500 or a kitty spur. I said, there's\Nsomething about that dog, 505. The fastest way to discover the intrinsic
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.17,0:07:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,reality of that which you are and the true nature of the universe is through\Nreverence. Through reverence for all of life, however it may appear to us at the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.88,0:08:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,moment. Each thing is being the best it can. You watch a videotape of a bank\Nrobber and you see he's got his mask on and he's waving his gun. I mean he's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,being the best possible bank robber he can be at the moment. He's doing a\Nmagnificent job. I mean some of them should be on Broadway. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.50,0:08:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,fantastic. He's acting out some fantasies, some positionality, and so it's\Nirrelevant to say whether what he's doing is good or bad. Good or bad has
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.84,0:08:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing to do with it. Somebody's got a gun in your head, let's not worry about\Ngood or bad. You see that mostly what
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you're doing is good or bad. You see that mostly what you're doing is good or bad. You see that mostly what\Nthe mind says about things is a luxury and when you're seeking enlightenment you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.09,0:09:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,have to forego the luxury of constant commentary on life and evaluation,\Nrighting and wronging it, trying to decide whether God is a liberal or
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.08,0:09:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,conservative. So we have some interesting new things today. We always have\Nnew things, but I don't want to shock people too much with too many new things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.79,0:09:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to eyes? All right, so let's do eyes. I was going to do movies today\Nand then I decided to do eyes. We did 150 movies at the end of which Susan couldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.95,0:10:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,lift her right arm for about a week. Devotional non-duality means devotion to truth, devotion to vintage,\Nto divinity as it reveals itself by truth. It means to witness the sacredness of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.79,0:10:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you treat all of life with reverence and witness the sacredness of all of life, you\Nwill soon identify yourself as the field and not the content of the field. Formally the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.75,0:10:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,project is to transcend the ego and one's identification with it. So I thought you'd\Nlike some new research we've done and we'll verify it this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.49,0:11:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We're speaking out of the other side of my mouth now? Yes. I'll speak out of the other side of my mouth.\NI'll have to be good enough the way I am. I'll have to look into that. We said that, we say all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.73,0:11:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that at all times the majority of the mind is actually silent. And so if we calibrate if that's\Ntrue, let's calibrate if that is true. At all times ninety-eight percent of the mind is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.37,0:11:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,silent.\NWhat we hear is the clatter of one or two percent. Ninety-eight percent of your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.76,0:12:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is silent at all times. So why complain about it? You're only talking about two percent.\NWell that cuts down the project, doesn't it? I just saved you ninety-eight percent of what
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.00,0:12:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you thought you were going to have to do. You're welcome. Yes.\NSo why does the, why does the remaining two percent seem to be such a problem? And we
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.37,0:12:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered it's because you are in a hypnotic state, hypnotized by that two percent. Resist.\NYou are in a trance. Resist. Everybody is in a hypnotic trance at the effect. You've
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.23,0:13:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,become the prisoner through hypnosis of that two percent. You've become entranced with\Nit, fascinated with it, and now you've let two percent of your mind run all of you. And
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.52,0:13:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not a good investment. Ninety-eight percent then would reveal the true nature\Nof reality. So when I say try to find the silent part of your mind, first of all you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.39,0:13:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have to know it exists. Right at this moment, right before you just had that last thought,\Nyour mind was silent. Yep, and now it's silent again. And now it's silent again. And then
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.48,0:13:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a little word goes across.\NHypnotic state. One can pray to God to relieve you and return you to sanity from being at
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.70,0:14:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the effect of hypnosis, a hypnotic trance from the content of one's mind, and pray for\Nliberation. Liberation means to be liberated from the illusion that you are the two percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.42,0:14:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see where the two percent gets its juice from. Huh. If nonduality is, you know, the\Nstate of enlightenment, then duality would be the state one wishes to transcend. So we
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.95,0:14:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,found the way through the eyes. The I-Z-E of life. We polarize, stems from the process\Nthat we're going to call eyes. This two percent eyes-es you all the time. And how does it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.50,0:15:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,eyes you? Well, you'll see. When it looks at something out there, it has the habit of\Npoliticizing it. Everywhere I speak, everybody asks me to do George Bush. What do they think
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.14,0:15:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,he's going to come out? Ninety-two or something? Not the same as Roosevelt, Truman, the same\Nas every other president. Okay, so we ask, is God a liberal? We go, no, he's not. The
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.62,0:15:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha said, wisdom is the middle way. Okay. All right. Because either extreme is insanity,\Nright? So politicize then causes dissension and conversation in your mind. You read the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.62,0:15:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,paper, you argue with the news, you argue with the editorial writer. So to politicize\Nis instantly to create a duality and create conflict. That's one of the great enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.30,0:16:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of peace. The next great enemy of peace is to moralize. So if we politicize and moralize,\Nwhich is everybody's habit when they read the paper or watch the news, you can see why
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.24,0:16:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is divided into good or bad.\NMoralize. What if you didn't moralize? What if you were just the witness? Let's say you're
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.37,0:16:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,from another planet, another galaxy, and you're here to witness the phenomena in this place\Nand report back, but all you can say is things seem to be happening. Things go up, things
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.75,0:16:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,go down, things live, they fall over, something is born, they clap or they cry, depending\Non the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.35,0:16:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhen it passes out of existence and they call it dying,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.33,0:17:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,people clap or cry depending on the circumstances.\NGlad to see that one go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.42,0:17:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The best thing he did for mankind is pass on it.\NWell, you say it shouldn't be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.26,0:17:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't be.\NThe best way to politicize is to moralize and idealize.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.44,0:17:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't be.\NNow you get on a soapbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.38,0:17:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the soapbox eyes, a great trap.\NOnce you get your ankle in it, it's very hard to get it out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.38,0:17:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because any way you move, you trigger another response.\NOnce you're in duality, every move triggers a response.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.91,0:17:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you decide you're wrong and back up,\Nyou will now be attacked for changing your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.15,0:17:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and backing up.\NAnd if you don't, you'd be criticized
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.05,0:17:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for not having done it.\NSo it's a no-win situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.94,0:18:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd once you get into duality, you cannot win.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.38,0:18:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you win, you will get punished, highly taxed,\Nand criticized.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.34,0:18:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe be bombed and assassinated.\NWhat's the explanation for 9-11?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.53,0:18:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Americans work hard, save their money,\Nand try to live an integrous life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.24,0:18:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That made them hate us.\NWell, because America had wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.54,0:18:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you get wealth?\NYou work your butt off, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.24,0:18:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo if you're political.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.98,0:18:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're politicized and moralized and then idealized,\Nyou've set up the next war.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.43,0:18:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the basis of war right there.\NWar has nothing to do with guns, munitions, bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.19,0:18:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are just the aftermath, the mechanics of it.\NOnce two guys decide how they're going to kill each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.84,0:18:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't make any difference whether you use swords, guns.\NI mean, the weaponry is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.90,0:19:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking around for weaponry is a real waste of time.\NSo I worry about this guy, I'll have to search through his 10
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.57,0:19:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and see if he's got a dagger in there.\NI don't think I want to worry about whether he's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.79,0:19:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,got a dagger in there, because I'm\Nreading where this guy's at, and he's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.35,0:19:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,going to get me one way or the other, you know what I mean?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.15,0:19:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So we politicize, we moralize, we idealize.\NAnd this is how we set up war.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.58,0:19:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what war comes out of, the first three items.\NThen out of that, we speculate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.42,0:19:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we begin to hypothesize.\NIt should be this way, it could be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.17,0:19:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,People ask you the hypothetical question, but what if?\NNever answer what if.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.14,0:19:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two questions you never answer.\NOne is why, and the other is what if.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.69,0:19:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the bear traps, all set for you.\NThe minute somebody says what if, you know they're out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.25,0:20:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to get you in their bear trap.\NWhat if?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.22,0:20:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if?\NBut what if everybody ate an ice cream cone
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.14,0:20:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time on the planet?\NWouldn't that cause a shortage of, I mean, you know what I
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.48,0:20:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,mean?\NThe hypothetical has absolutely no grounding in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.55,0:20:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The hypothetical is the grossly distorted pseudo-scientific\Nstudies that prove that this is dangerous, or that's dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.77,0:20:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or this is dangerous, and keeps everybody frightened,\Nand programs everybody with negative programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.26,0:20:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't so before, everybody's believing it,\Nand makes it happen now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.22,0:20:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As you know, you've done the course of miracles.\NYou're subject to that which you hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.01,0:20:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you think this is going to kill you, it's going to.\NActually, there's no way around it anyway, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.72,0:21:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because statistics show more people who ride in the passenger seat die than in the rear\Nseat, therefore you better not sit in the passenger seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.36,0:21:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,However, more people who sit on the right-hand side in the passenger back seat die than on\Nthe left side.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.41,0:21:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't sit on the right side either.\NMore people who park on highways get killed on the highway than park in parking lots.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.38,0:21:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,lot so you can't park in there. You get what I'm saying? More people die in the\Nbathroom than die in the kitchen so you can't go in the bathroom. Then you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.24,0:21:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,gotta go to the bathroom and then you find out more people get killed in the\Nkitchen than do in the bedroom. You got to stay in the bedroom. More people get
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.77,0:21:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,killed coming down from the second floor bedroom than the first floor bedroom so\Nyou can see how if you're gonna run your life by hypothetical
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.94,0:21:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,statistics it gets really awkward, you know what I'm saying? The best thing to do is\Nlive your life as you see it this way you can and you remember from previous
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.49,0:22:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,research that the time of your death is already preset so there's no trying to\Nno point trying to doubt guess God. Karmically the time is determined at the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.72,0:22:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,moment you are born. We reaffirm that is a fact the Lord. That is a fact we\Nreaffirmed in every lecture. You don't have to worry about death because it's
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.85,0:22:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,already taken care of. The other thing you have to worry about is you're never\Ngoing to experience your own death.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.49,0:22:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway it's not possible. The instant of death, bang, you're out of the body, you\Nwitness it, you feel sorry for the people there but you're fine. I should have done
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.59,0:22:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,this a long time ago, comes to you. That motorcycle accident, I should have said\Nto hell with the respirator and anyway. So you see the karmic unfoldment then of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.90,0:22:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality. Karma then is, you're not controlled by karma but it does set up\Nlet's say a condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.38,0:23:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say extreme guilt over something you've done in some lifetime gets you left\Nin a hot car, a little toddler with the windows closed and after an hour you're dead. Everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.80,0:23:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,sentimentalizes about that. Oh poor little tyke. If you look at poor little tyke in a\Nprevious lifetime you won't think it's poor little tyke. What is the karmic consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.09,0:23:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of that?\NSee either everything is happening by accident which would negate the possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.81,0:23:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity or nothing is happening by accident because accidents are not possible. An accident\Nreally denotes an intellectual limitation. What it means is you don't understand the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.66,0:24:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons for it. In the infinite power of divinity no such thing as an accident is possible. This\Ncomes around.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.57,0:24:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Here swoops down there and in my own lifetime having gone through extreme agony out of a karmic\Nobligation which I've already told you about, the recall of the reason for what I was going
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.70,0:24:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,through was clear as a bell. You remembered the extreme guilt about not having killed that guy,\Nnot having killed him. The warrior I wounded in the groin and left him to die of the wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.79,0:24:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have put him to sleep and didn't though. I was in linha infirmum and brought\Na herniography with no anesthesia once I햇rproud. Which wouldn't recommend unless you have
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.22,0:25:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,gored someone to death and still feel guilty about it. In this case you will have undone\Nthat guilt by the time you're through.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.59,0:25:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity means that one can grab sort of the overall context, divinity field out of which\Nuniverse happens with
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.65,0:25:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,within it is evolving. The quickest way to do it\Nis to look over great expanses of time. Look over great expanses
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.74,0:25:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of time. Don't look at just this little thing. But that this little thing\Nis happening, you know, in a progression of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.24,0:25:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,time that runs millions of years.\NAll right, so we hypothesize
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.60,0:26:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of hypothesis\Nwe get all kinds of fallacious answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.68,0:26:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The next thing we do is we romanticize. We romanticize\Nabout all kinds of things and create a flowery
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.75,0:26:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,imagination of how it could be, should be,\Nand then become dissatisfied if
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.21,0:26:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it does not compare favorably with our\Nromanticization of it. So to romanticize
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.36,0:26:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that,\Nwhat we do is to project onto it. So all these
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.74,0:26:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,examples you see,\Nsomething is happening out there, and then the mind projects this
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.90,0:26:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,interpretation\Nonto it. Then believes that what it just projected onto the world is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.35,0:26:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,out there.\NSo through this little example, you'll quickly see
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.25,0:26:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that any commentary you can make about life is\Nalways a projection. Because when you experience a rejection,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.94,0:27:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing to say about it.\NThere's nothing to say about it. It just is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.00,0:27:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So to romanticize, then, is to set oneself up for fallacy.\NTo elaborate, where no elaboration is really necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.24,0:27:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It means to exaggerate certain qualities.\NTo romanticize, you have to distort it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.92,0:27:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As compared to romanticizing, you have to distort it.\NTo romanticize, there's reverence.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.49,0:27:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's reverence for the beauty of a relationship.\NThere's reverence for the intrinsic innocence of the animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.91,0:27:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to romanticize it, which\Nmeans to distort and to exaggerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.39,0:28:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The next one is rather obvious.\NAnd, of course, it follows from the previous ones. To criticize,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.47,0:28:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, is,\Nis a rather glaring, obvious ego function.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.25,0:28:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This should be that. They shouldn't have done this.\NThey should have done this. They shouldn't have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.25,0:28:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can look at the black beetle laying on his back,\Nhis little legs wanging around in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.25,0:28:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, you shouldn't have done that.\NYou should have looked where you're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.25,0:28:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't have walked...\NSo you can see how absurd criticize is.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.35,0:28:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So at the end, we're going to give you a little mnemonic.\NThe fastest way to God is to become aware of the eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.82,0:28:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that your mind is eysing out there,\Nand thereby become wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.30,0:29:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo the progression through the ego is primarily one of self-observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.35,0:29:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And many teachers, you know, say the same thing.\NI think it was Mr. Gadara Maharaj.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.80,0:29:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They would tell the students, watch the mind.\NWatch the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.40,0:29:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if that worked or not.\NIn what way?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.20,0:29:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to define in what way.\NYou watch how it begins to criticize,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.19,0:29:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and you watch how it begins to emotionalize.\NSee, first it politicizes, then it moralizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.85,0:29:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,then it idealizes, then it hypothesizes,\Nthen it romanticizes, then it criticizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.90,0:29:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it goes into indignation.\NEmotionalizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.90,0:29:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Or oo-ah.\NSentimentalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.40,0:29:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sentimentalism.\NPoor baby in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.61,0:30:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Wah, wah, wah.\NCries over everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.86,0:30:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it's indignant over everything.\NIt sees everything as tragedy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.01,0:30:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,or something that needs to be corrected.\NAnd who should correct what is criticized?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.33,0:30:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Who should do that?\NYou.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.06,0:30:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You should take care of it.\NAnd how are you going to take care of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.06,0:30:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to take care of it by telling the people\Nwho are wrong how wrong they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.02,0:30:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And how they should have done it.\NEverybody tries that with their spouse, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.22,0:30:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And the children, your mother-in-law.\NYou know he doesn't like blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.01,0:30:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and you bought him the blue shirts.\NSo we emotionalize.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.47,0:30:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalize is another form of exaggeration.\NEmotionalizing is exaggerating.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.77,0:31:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalizing is a way to dramatize.\NDramatize.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.04,0:31:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're connected with reality, let's say,\Nand somebody says, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.00,0:31:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you're probably going to die of this thing\Nin a couple of days or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.17,0:31:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good. Glad you told me.\NI'll call and shut the phone off
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.05,0:31:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell them to hold the mail.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.27,0:31:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's to emotionalize about?\NYou want to emotionalize because you want to dramatize.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.92,0:31:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to dramatize.\NSo emotionalizing is trying to make things bigger than they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.68,0:31:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I see somebody in the office.\NShe's all broken down and crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.68,0:31:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She's carrying on.\NI said, what's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.85,0:31:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother-in-law is having her gallbladder out.\NShe said, help me God.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.47,0:31:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what she says.\NWhy is she blubbering all over the place
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.59,0:32:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's her mother-in-law having her gallbladder out?\NYou see, the poor boundaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.05,0:32:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The poor boundaries.\NThe dog is sick, so you're depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.29,0:32:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The bird gets hit by the windshield of the car.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.68,0:32:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you're the windshield.\NSometimes you're the bug, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.48,0:32:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened just recently.\NDriving along at high speed and all of a sudden a bird flew right into the windshield.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.50,0:32:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye-bye birdie.\NThe only concern was that she would be upset by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.90,0:32:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it is shocking if you run over an animal by mistake.\NEverybody who's done it knows it's sort of a horrible feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.33,0:32:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we see that the mind, the 2% then,\Nhow does it become so dominant?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.29,0:33:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the mechanisms by which it becomes dominant.\NIt's opinionated about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.69,0:33:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always right and wronging things.\NThat creates enemies and friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.69,0:33:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It idealizes how it should be, which of course it can't be or it would be.\NIt hypothesizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.46,0:33:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at the nature of the world we live in\Nand understand what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.49,0:33:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there would be no point to change it.\NThe human world we live in is the ultimate perfect place
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.36,0:33:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,for spiritual evolution, just as it is.\NEverything is as it is because it offers the most possible alternatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.53,0:34:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It offers the greatest karmic opportunity.\NAlmost from instant to instant one can say yes or no, yes or no.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.84,0:34:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,One can reverence life or despise it.\NOne can curse or bless.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.84,0:34:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Every instant then.\NSo the soul, I always liken it to an iron filing,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.42,0:34:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, with polarity and a charge on it and all, or a molecule.\NSo every moment this little molecule is saying yes to this, no to this,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.03,0:34:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,yes to this.\NLast night the story of the ocean depths was on.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.03,0:34:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a stunningly beautiful thing\Nin which you see these incredible things floating through the air like this
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.42,0:34:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's long.\NAnd at the same time it's luminescent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.57,0:34:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's incredible beauty, incredible beauty.\NIncredible beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.61,0:35:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When you don't project criticism, romanticism,\Nwhen you just witness these little, smaller than protozoa or whatever they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.92,0:35:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't get the name of them.\NTheir beauty was too great.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.92,0:35:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to call them anything.\NAnd like little umbrellas that go like this, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.50,0:35:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just entrancing, magnificently, incredibly beautiful.\NA couple thousand feet below the sea is a world of incredible beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.78,0:35:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And it also, and they also eat each other.\NIsn't that awful?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.38,0:35:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, because if you don't get eaten, you don't get to evolve into something else.\NIf somebody doesn't eat the cow, the cow's spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.38,0:35:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,how will it birth itself as a living entity in a world of life?\NIf everybody becomes a vegetarian, what should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.90,0:36:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill all the cattle, let them die of old age, you know?\NMillions of cattle won't be out there going moo.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.82,0:36:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I go to the girl's ranch in the morning, I pass through a herd of them.\NAnd I'll stop and say hello to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.09,0:36:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They stand there and look at you, go on by, you know.\NAnd I also have to stop and greet them and tell them good morning, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.32,0:36:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I tell them, if it wasn't for McDonald's, you wouldn't be here.\NYou see, if you don't do all of this, then you can just love the cow
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.07,0:36:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that somehow its spirit evolved by being of service,\Nby laying down its life for some kind of a higher creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.17,0:36:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And somehow, because the evolution of consciousness then proceeds\Nover vast amounts of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.75,0:37:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and expresses itself in a great multitude of life forms,\Nand of course when we calibrate the energy fields of living things
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.17,0:37:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,starting maybe 400 million years ago and coming on up,\Nyou see that consciousness is evolving.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.17,0:37:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, some horse has got to become a cow, doesn't it?\NIt has to become a mammalian, which births,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.40,0:37:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,which then releases the maternal,\Nwhich begins to express love and nurturance.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.59,0:37:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see love and nurturance in the dragon family.\NYou've got to be a cow, you've got to be a sheep,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.71,0:37:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to be a bird, care about the egg.\NSomewhere in evolution you've got to come out of the reptilian,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.13,0:38:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates very low.\NThe Komodo dragon is still around, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.05,0:38:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does love birth itself on the planet?\NYou can't do it through a Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.57,0:38:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Komodo dragon automatically kills you\Nbecause it doesn't know any other way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.17,0:38:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It just bites you and it waits until you die, see?\NThat's as far as it could go in evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.92,0:38:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see a Komodo dragon becoming a warm mother cat.\NNo, it stays a Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.71,0:38:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Something else comes off and evolves and evolves.\NThe world as we see it is perfect, perfect, perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.01,0:38:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to change it.\NAnd the world that you bemoan is all a projection.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.86,0:38:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it too bad? Isn't that sad? Shouldn't that be better?\NDon't you see those are all mentations?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.13,0:39:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All mentations, those are all mentations.\NIf you stop the mentations, you merely witness it as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.03,0:39:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So we like to emotionalize and dramatize\Nand in doing that we exaggerate
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.03,0:39:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and now everything becomes a catastrophe.\NCatastrophize.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.82,0:39:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is a catastrophe.\NThe newspapers specialize in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.94,0:39:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The news channels love catastrophes.\NThey can't get to a big accident fast enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.26,0:39:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Fourteen people killed on a so-and-so.\NMan, the helicopters are right out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.26,0:39:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just sucking up the drama of the catastrophe.\NGrinding it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.59,0:39:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Catastrophe.\NSo to exaggerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.30,0:39:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Say your mother-in-law is having her gallbladder out.\NSo?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.30,0:39:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not going to do it while she's awake.\NShe's going to have Demerol afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.50,0:39:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She's going to have sterile fields.\NShe's going to have stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.57,0:39:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Our great-grandmothers didn't have,\Nor my grandmother didn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.57,0:40:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They were lucky if they survived surgery.\NLucky if they survived surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.53,0:40:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She's going to have anesthesia, which is more than I had.\NSo we catastrophize and we dramatize.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.57,0:40:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We say this world should be a different world.\NAnd we begin to theorize about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.69,0:40:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how we're going to change it.\NThis is the new direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.82,0:40:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And we theorize.\NAnd universities are great at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.11,0:40:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWe just calibrated all the universities last weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.42,0:40:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThe Big Ten, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.42,0:40:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Come out really about the highest.\NBig Ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.80,0:40:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Ten universities.\NCome out higher than the Ivy League.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.80,0:40:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.53,0:40:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So we begin to theorize about how we could\Nsolve men's problems, what we conceive as problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.69,0:40:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, because there isn't a problem there,\Nor any solution that you can come up with
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.78,0:41:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Ncoerce the world into following is going to be disastrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.78,0:41:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have Marxism.\NYou have all these isms, which are all hypothetical solutions
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.78,0:41:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to hypothetical problems which don't exist.\NAll you can say is in every barrel of apples,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.17,0:41:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,some apples are going to be near the top\Nand some are going to be near the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.38,0:41:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Unavoidable.\NYou can say, well, it shouldn't be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.44,0:41:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All children should be able to run as fast as others.\NThat's how it should be, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.92,0:41:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus it in that way.\NI only got one F in my life, and that was in sports.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.19,0:41:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to bring my 50 cents or my towel card\Nfor the semester, and I got flunked.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.92,0:41:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And they used to have what they call field day.\NThat to me was horror day.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.23,0:42:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to try and think up a headache or a sick stomach.\NNo, you're going to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.19,0:42:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the things you had to do in sports day\Nis they would have a rope from the ceiling of the gymnasium,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.25,0:42:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and you would have to climb this freaking rope.\NSecond.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.07,0:42:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I never got past the middle of the rope much to the top.\NIs that fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.84,0:42:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, mesomorphs are going up there like this.\NNot fair that I wasn't born a mesomorph.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.01,0:42:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a young gentleman here who I love dearly.\NHe was a great fan of ours, and he is a mesomorph.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.09,0:42:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And every time I hug him, I say, God, that's incredible.\NThis guy can probably lift a safe or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.15,0:42:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NAnd I'm having trouble opening a package of light bulbs
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.15,0:42:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from the dime store.\NI can't get through the plastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.15,0:43:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that fair?\NRecently we did a recording for a big company,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.07,0:43:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the people that came from the company,\Nthe vice president of the company, was 6'6".
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.53,0:43:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking up at him like this.\NIs that fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.23,0:43:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the fun things about being in Korea is the average height there.\NThe average height there is much less than here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.32,0:43:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I was in Korea,\NI got to feel what it's like to be a tall guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.61,0:43:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's head's about this high.\NThen you feel like Mr. Big.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.26,0:43:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that fair?\NHypothesize. Is that fair?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.98,0:43:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not right.\NAnd I've got a political solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.98,0:44:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's going to get chopped off at the same level.\NThe Bantus and the Watusi, so help me God, did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.46,0:44:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Historical fact.\NThe Bantus cut the Watusi's legs off in their war.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.61,0:44:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're all the same size.\NSo that's catastrophizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.07,0:44:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of that we theorize wondrous solutions.\NAnd we do that by intellectualizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.13,0:44:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, rationalize is making excuses.\NEverybody knows that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.46,0:44:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All these things that we're talking about today,\Nif you witness your mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.46,0:44:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see it's doing one or the other of these things all the time.\NIt doesn't hold you in thralldom.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.50,0:44:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,By being stupid.\NIt has fascinating dilemmas, fascinating solutions,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.09,0:44:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,great dramas, great emotions.\NAll right, so we rationalize our behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.57,0:44:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We rationalize.\NThis is a three-year-old.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.57,0:45:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You say to the three-year-old,\Ndid you knock that over?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.26,0:45:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't do it, Mom.\NThe cat did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.28,0:45:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuses.\NSo that's the world of excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.42,0:45:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuses are a waste of time.\NBut it satisfies the three-year-old in us.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.42,0:45:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we've created such an impossible dilemma for ourself now,\Nwe need relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.53,0:45:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's called fantasize.\NYou go to the movies, you read the novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.55,0:45:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We daydream and we fantasize\Nbecause we've made life so painful and unrewarding
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.90,0:45:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that we now have to create an imaginary world.\NWhere things are more dramatic, more right,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.90,0:46:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,more the way we want them to be.\NWe fantasize about how it should be, could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.73,0:46:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing we tend to do is infantilize.\NWe infantilize people.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.73,0:46:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always political solutions to non-problems\Nbecause we've infantilized the people
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.73,0:46:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and pictured that they're helpless and hopeless.\NAnd now we can be the good person
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.05,0:46:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and come in and bail them out.\NBail them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.13,0:46:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of the first step in Al-Anon\Nand those types of recovery programs
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.61,0:46:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is to allow them to sink on their own.\NIf they're going down the tubes,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.53,0:46:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,cheer them on.\NThey're going down the tubes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.48,0:46:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the only way you can hit bottom\Nis by going down the tubes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.65,0:46:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you infantilize them\Nand see them as helpless and hopeless
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.80,0:47:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to support them and hold them up,\Nyou can keep them physically surviving
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.80,0:47:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,long past the endpoint.\NAnd their recovery then is allowing them
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.21,0:47:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to take responsibility for their own actions.\NWe rationalize and then another form of that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.25,0:47:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is called intellectualize.\NThis is why some of the universities
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.40,0:47:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't come out too well.\NIf you're in the practice of medicine,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.40,0:47:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,this one is the one that really blows you away.\NBecause the massive dilemma of practicing medicine
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.69,0:47:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is all coming out of intellectualization.\NIntellectualization.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.03,0:47:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently the government passed some new regulation,\Nwhich was totally, completely fraudulent,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.03,0:47:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,called the HIPAA regulation.\NH-I-P-P-A.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.32,0:47:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The public thinks that the privacy of their medical records\Nis now being protected by these HIPAA regulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.61,0:48:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No, quite the contrary is true.\NSince the time of Hippocrates,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.61,0:48:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,every doctor has guarded the privacy\Nof his patient's information.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.61,0:48:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, a lot of them will go to jail\Nrather than review it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.61,0:48:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And they have periodically.\NNo, what they've actually done with the Privacy Act
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.71,0:48:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is make your medical records available to anybody.\NAny company, anybody with a vested interest
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.44,0:48:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in your health, welfare, etc.,\Nnow has access to your medical records.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.73,0:48:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The great HIPAA Privacy Act was exactly the opposite.\NIt's the non-privacy act.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.73,0:48:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're not gaining privacy, you're losing it.\NIsn't that interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.03,0:48:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You could do all that in one sentence.\NWell, for months and years I've been getting piles.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.65,0:48:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,My HIPAA file, I am not kidding, is this thick.\NThis is all bulletins and issues and regulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.84,0:48:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The granddaddy of them all came last week.\NIt's a whole notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.84,0:49:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnificent production.\NAnd if I sign this and return it to the company,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.38,0:49:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,they will give me a certificate saying\Nthat I'm complying with the HIPAA regulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.71,0:49:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They never heard of Hippocrates.\NThey never heard of the oath of Hippocrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.94,0:49:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know a single doctor that doesn't guard\Nhis patients with a paranoid ferocity.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.23,0:49:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So that all comes out of intellectualize.\NAnd the one thing about intellectualize
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.30,0:49:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is the more complicated you can make it, the better.\NSo that Medicare regulations run 10,000 pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.51,0:49:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,10,000 pages.\NSo the proliferation of complexity then
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.86,0:49:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out of intellectualizations\Nand also, sorry, legal experience in courts.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.19,0:50:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That everything has to be documented\Nto the point of absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.19,0:50:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And for some years,\NI was the only psychiatrist that would go around
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.28,0:50:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to the nursing homes.\NSo I saw zillions of old people.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.28,0:50:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And their charts were magnificent.\NHere's this old lady who doesn't say anything
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.28,0:50:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or do anything.\NShe takes a couple pills a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.28,0:50:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And her chart is this thick.\NWeighs 10 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.86,0:50:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time she goes to the bathroom,\Nasks for a glass of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.05,0:50:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has to sign for everything.\NThe intellectualization then.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.46,0:50:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, everybody's complaining\Nabout the cost of medical care.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.46,0:50:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NJust remember that from the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.46,0:50:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the cost of medical care is 9% is the physician's fee.\NThe rest is bureaucracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.46,0:50:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,9% of the total medical bill is the physician.\N93% comes out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.46,0:50:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes out of this plus what if.\NWell, what if you didn't document
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.61,0:51:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that you went to the bathroom?\NShe might die of constipation.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.05,0:51:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be sued for death by constipation.\NIn as much as we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.09,0:51:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically, when she's supposed to leave this world\Nis set already.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.21,0:51:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,To even blame anybody is,\Nfrom a higher viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.21,0:51:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, idiotic.\NNothing causes anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.21,0:51:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing causes anything else.\NSo intellectualize then means to complicate things
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.21,0:51:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so they become cumbersome and manageable,\Ninefficient, and extremely costly.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.21,0:51:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Extremely costly.\NPeople worry about the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.13,0:51:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all kinds of people always predicting\Nthe end of the world, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.13,0:51:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always a workshop somewhere\Non the end of the world about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.53,0:51:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And people don't really know\Nhow the end of the world is going to come about,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.59,0:52:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but I do.\NA giant massive gridlock
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.59,0:52:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes so overwhelming\Nthat finally a complete paralysis,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.59,0:52:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing can move any further\Nbecause all the regulations make it so that if you...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.59,0:52:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday I was trying to get an older patient\Ninto an emergency into the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.05,0:52:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in Cottonwood, Verde Valley Medical Center.\NAnd the complexity of such a simple accomplishment,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.46,0:52:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nit's better to let them die, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.26,0:52:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NBefore this intellectualization
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.65,0:52:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,caused such enormous complexity,\Nwhen I had a huge practice,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.05,0:53:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd call the hospital and say,\Nthis guy's coming in, send the ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.05,0:53:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it took.\NNow it takes me dozens of phone calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.05,0:53:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on the phone for hours\Ntrying to get through the bureaucratic complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.05,0:53:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And actually a person could have died\Nlong before you get them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.05,0:53:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This complexity.\NSo everything then...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.50,0:53:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You eventually hit a gridlock, a log jam,\Nwhere effective functioning becomes almost impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.73,0:53:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And apparently that's what happened before 9-11.\NThe government agencies were so bogged down
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.73,0:53:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,with their interfacing rules.\NYou can't speak to him
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.73,0:53:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you get permission from so-and-so,\Nbut that's against Rule 62 and you have...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.73,0:53:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So finally it just became stultified.\NAll the information was there,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.73,0:53:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but nobody had, like, permission.\NI don't have permission to call him and tell him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.75,0:53:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a permission.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.28,0:54:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So intellectualize then means eventually great complexity.\NAnd it's the whole process is mentalizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.53,0:54:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say the way to enlightenment is to observe,\Nthat your mind is constantly mentalizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.90,0:54:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What you think is out there is a mentalization.\NThe belief in causation, causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.50,0:54:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm, right and wrong,\Nthese are all mentalizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.78,0:54:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They only exist as the thought.\NAll these things that you presume exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.61,0:54:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot find in the world.\NYou can only find them as a thought process.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.00,0:54:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They have no concordant reality,\Nno concordant reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.00,0:54:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So mentalizing then is what the 2% is doing,\Nkeeping us hypnotized by the process,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.15,0:55:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the process, the phenomena,\Nall these indignations,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.50,0:55:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,moralization,\Nromanticization,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.50,0:55:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,erotization.\NI didn't put that up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.50,0:55:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Erotization.\NYeah, a lot of that going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.90,0:55:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And fantasize, mentalize,\Nand then, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.90,0:55:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we said idealize,\Nand it went up there twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.90,0:55:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be serious.\NBecause this is how it should be,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.09,0:55:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is how it should be.\NSo I guess how it should be must have been the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.71,0:55:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when I wrote that list.\NThis is how the list should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.05,0:55:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I better have idealized on there.\NWell, I'm glad I got it up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.90,0:55:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we get to another great trap.\NAnd this one is a little harder to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.61,0:56:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something people don't realize\Ngoes on all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.82,0:56:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is called glamorize.\NGlamorize is somewhat a product of emotionalize
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.38,0:56:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and romanticize and idealize.\NWe glamorize phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.46,0:56:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We glamorize political positions.\NThe way you give this firepower
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.46,0:56:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is you glamorize it.\NYou glamorize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.00,0:56:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You give it pseudo-importance.\NYou get somebody with a big name.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.32,0:56:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You present it as a dramatic presentation\Nwith all kinds of color and a full orchestra.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.53,0:56:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever watch some nature program on television?\NAnd while this nature program is going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.53,0:56:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all this dramatic music is going on in the background.\NI can't hear what the announcer is talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.53,0:56:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, when they're showing an ant walking across a leaf,\Ndo you have to have this drama music in the background?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.82,0:57:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that ever annoy you?\NThere's drama music put in as background to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.78,0:57:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that should be incredibly of themselves,\Noverwhelmingly beautiful,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.13,0:57:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,now are brought down by what the producer thinks.\NSo you get this drama music in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.96,0:57:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Da-dum, da-dum, da-dum, da-dum.\NSometimes just a fly going along.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.96,0:57:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's this drama music.\NYou would think this is the end of the world about to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.96,0:57:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dramatization, the romanticization,\Nthen leads to a glamorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.44,0:57:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So many political positions and many ideologies\Nbecome glamorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.73,0:57:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamorized.\NWorkers unite.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.32,0:57:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You have nothing to lose but your chains.\NBoy, that sounds great, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.32,0:57:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't get you out to the barricades.\NYou've got no heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.63,0:58:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're out to the barricades, you've got no head.\NBecause you're just going to get blown away.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.63,0:58:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And frankly, everything's going to go back the way it was before anyway.\NAnyway, you can go down as a hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.82,0:58:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's a glamorization right there.\NTo glamorize, again, means to make it bigger than life,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.46,0:58:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to overemphasize,\Nto make that which is less than salutary a pure attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.69,0:58:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,M.T.V., of course, is the stunning ultimate example of that.\NAnd various video games.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.98,0:58:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Some video games are so incredibly non-integrist\Nthat I don't want to even describe what they're about.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.36,0:58:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, nobody would produce anything like that.\NNor would anybody buy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.36,0:58:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you find it's the biggest seller.\NThe biggest seller.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.78,0:58:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The glamorization of that which the world calls evil, then,\Nis glamorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.46,0:59:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It, of course, fills up the TV channels every night.\NThe glamorization of all the criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.46,0:59:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Bonnie and Clyde,\Nthey become romanticized and glamorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.50,0:59:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they're attractive.\NYou say, how do these young kids all get into lives of crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.82,0:59:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would they want to do that?\NBecause it's glamorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.88,0:59:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You wear your hat this way, right?\NYou collect all the symbols, the gang symbols.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.42,0:59:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You be Mr. Tough.\NMr. Tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.73,0:59:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Make big money doing drugs.\NThat's very glamorous.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.94,0:59:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside of glamor is that it is something sprayed onto life\Nto make it look attractive.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.34,0:59:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you take that away, you see it's quite ugly.\NQuite ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.34,0:59:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite ugly.\NThe next thing the mind does is demonize everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.55,0:59:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It likes to do that out of politicize, moralize, and idealize.\NThe next thing it does is want to demonize.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.75,1:00:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And we said the way around that is to catch your mind at it.\NYou see, if you're pro-vanilla,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.19,1:00:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't mean you have to kill chocolate.\NYou don't have to get up the barricades and the machine guns.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.30,1:00:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to assassinate chocolate.\NI hate chocolate clubs.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.13,1:00:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can declare chocolate is un-American.\NIt's not fair to the great masses.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.86,1:00:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's elitism.\NIt's elitist.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.46,1:00:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Vanilla is the flavor of the masses.\NAnd chocolate is the fete elite.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.09,1:00:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we can demonize anything.\NOf course, we know that everything is bad for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.61,1:01:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think something is not bad for you, it's because you haven't heard yet.\NEverything is fatal.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.38,1:01:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything you eat will kill you.\NYesterday's psychiatric newspaper I'm reading, it says,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.71,1:01:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain antidepressant makes people depressed.\NI've used it for 20 years and a thousand people.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.00,1:01:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I never saw anybody get depressed on this.\NWhat it means is the guy doesn't understand what he's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.90,1:01:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Prozac went through the same thing.\NIt caused people to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.57,1:01:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They misdiagnosed the depression.\NIt was actually a bipolar depression.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.57,1:01:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they relieved the depression,\Nthe person now had the energy to kill himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.57,1:02:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,To kill an undiagnosed bipolar is to give them an antidepressant.\NNow he feels good and he can do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.17,1:02:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But the naivete of the press is unbelievable.\NAnd when you read the press,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.46,1:02:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to notice something unique that will help you\Nundo your fascination with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.55,1:02:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice there's always a writer.\NYou ever notice that?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.42,1:02:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just a story by Ellen Lou Smith,\NMary Jane Peabody, Jack Collier.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.57,1:02:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't the news.\NThis is a story written by some yokai.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.76,1:02:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A local who doesn't know anything about the news.\NI guarantee that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.19,1:02:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,An article about psychiatry is not written by a psychiatrist.\NIt's written by Jack Peabody.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.61,1:02:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that.\NI want you to notice the authority that we give
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.61,1:03:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to what we think is news is nothing but a story.\NThere's an internet address I could give you,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.34,1:03:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but I forgot it.\NAll the media, the articles they want
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.61,1:03:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,on all different kinds of subjects.\NHow to bake a cake, how to kill an Arab,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.86,1:03:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,how to cure your own pneumonia.\NThere's something out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.11,1:03:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It lists page after page.\NArticles wanted by all the media out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.11,1:03:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So some joker who's a writer sits down,\Nhe pulls out some data,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.30,1:03:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a little bit of data from here and there,\Nand he quickly writes an article.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.30,1:03:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it becomes the authority.\NWe live our life imprisoned by fear
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.36,1:03:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,created by the lack of understanding\Nof writers who don't get the depth and the background
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.36,1:03:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and comprehension of what they're writing about.\NAnd it now becomes called truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.36,1:03:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That more people were killed in one passenger car\Nthan the other means none of us can sit in that seat anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.32,1:03:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, is that a conclusion or what?\NIs that stupidity?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.48,1:04:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo then we intellectualize, we mentalize,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.63,1:04:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we idealize, we glamorize.\NNow we demonize things.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.63,1:04:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We get into the chocolate and vanilla problem.\NSee, once we redefine these things,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.11,1:04:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see they're not that difficult to transcend.\NUnless you see through the illusion,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.11,1:04:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they're very difficult to transcend.\NVery difficult to transcend.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.21,1:04:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see hardly anybody becomes enlightened.\NHardly anybody even gets to 500, much less enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.21,1:04:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because these are formidable.\NYou know, they look simple to us
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.82,1:04:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when we put them up there and start taking them apart\Nbecause they're like pick-up sticks.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.82,1:04:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you begin to get the sense of it,\Nthese are all projectile.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.98,1:04:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all projections.\NThese are all imaginations.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.98,1:04:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all mentations.\NNone of that exists in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.94,1:05:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to challenge out there.\NYou can walk up to a tree and say,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.38,1:05:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,how come you look the way you look?\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.84,1:05:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,People like to argue with consciousness research.\NI said, it's like asking a tree,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.84,1:05:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,why are you what you are?\NI don't know, it just is that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.92,1:05:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we tend to demonize.\NAnd then the flip side of demonizing
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.92,1:05:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and making everything black and white\Nis we begin to prize.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.92,1:05:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We prize certain things.\NSo there it brings forth the solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.09,1:05:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and its wantingness.\NI'm proud to announce
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.59,1:05:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that I've given up my desire\Nfor a 1946
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.59,1:05:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Packard converter,\NCadillac convertible.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.61,1:05:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid somebody might give me one.\NThe way I got over it was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.57,1:06:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And its caliper went down the road.\NI don't want a 46 Lincoln-Continental anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.13,1:06:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, it was sleek.\NIt looked like 1936 in spades.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.53,1:06:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fantastic.\NRed on top of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.36,1:06:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll keep me in the world a while longer.\NYou've got to want something.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.76,1:06:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,At the last minute,\Nyou think of the Excalibur.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.38,1:06:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing all right\Nwhen you just got it down to an Excalibur.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.01,1:06:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we begin to prize.\NSo we could let that grow.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.01,1:06:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We could let that grow.\NAnd you can see how it's just
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.01,1:06:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,even one desire\Ncould begin to run your life,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.30,1:06:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to prize certain titles,\Ncertain addresses,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.30,1:06:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,certain lifestyles.\NIt becomes more important
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.46,1:06:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,than anything else.\NAnd, of course, success in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.63,1:07:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is what has been prized.\NIn the world I grew up,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.63,1:07:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world in which\Nalmost all of us grew up,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.63,1:07:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nwhat was prized was success.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.05,1:07:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The college degree,\Nthe good address,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.05,1:07:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,all the appurtenances,\Na reasonably new car.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.61,1:07:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Except, thank you,\Nyounger than 1984.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.19,1:07:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And we begin to prize those things,\Nand now they
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.23,1:07:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,run all of the world.\NThe last one is the greatest
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.90,1:07:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of them all.\NAnd this is the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.98,1:07:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,fabric of today's world.\NIt is victimized.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.71,1:07:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the\Nwondrous suction
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.75,1:07:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that pulls everybody into it.\NThe great victimization.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.03,1:07:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So these become,\Nall these become tools.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.07,1:07:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Tools of victimization.\NSo we have
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.13,1:08:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the incredible\Nlegalities that go on
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.46,1:08:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which can be heard on every night's television.\NThat somebody who
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.55,1:08:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,admittedly was witnessed to drive over\N18 people and kill them all
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.55,1:08:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is innocent because\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.14,1:08:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,he's a victim.\NYou see how the badge of victimhood
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.31,1:08:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is so sought after today.\NIt is the plushiest,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.51,1:08:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,juiciest plum.\NIf you can become victim,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.60,1:08:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you got this world by you know what.\NThe race to be victim is
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.81,1:08:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,rapid.\NEveryone pictures themselves as victim
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.42,1:08:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's great competition\Nin victimhood
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.42,1:08:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to see who is the biggest victim.\NThe way the story goes
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.67,1:08:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll see what happens with victim.\NA cop's walking down the street
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.22,1:09:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and he hears a rustling.\NHe goes in and says, young man, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.22,1:09:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The man goes like this.\NThe cop shoots him.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.56,1:09:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the kid is now the victim.\NThen the cop gets sued.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.57,1:09:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's the victim.\NHowever, in the meantime,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.47,1:09:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the kid gets drunk and kills somebody else\Nwho is now the victim
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.10,1:09:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and goes to court.\NThe witness now becomes the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.67,1:09:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the victim?\NYou see it's like a ball bouncing around.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.67,1:09:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever it hits is now the next victim.\NThe victim of the judiciary,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.77,1:09:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the victim of the perjury.\NEverybody is the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.07,1:09:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The 9-11 bombers are victims.\NI'm sure if they hadn't died
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.07,1:09:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there'd be parades of lawyers\Ntalking about how their civil rights
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.07,1:09:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,are being violated.\NNever mind 3,000 people
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.07,1:10:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,blown out of the sky.\NSo the game of victim now,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.07,1:10:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody gets to be victim.\NEvery legal situation,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.18,1:10:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,every political situation\Nis a trade-off on
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.23,1:10:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,who is the victim.\NWho is the victim?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.61,1:10:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That comes right out of politicizing,\Nmoralizing, idealizing,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.61,1:10:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothesizing, criticizing.\NIt comes out of all of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.84,1:10:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So victimization now\Nis the world's
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.84,1:10:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,biggest problem.\NEverybody is the victim
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.38,1:10:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of something else.\NI'm the victim of not being
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.38,1:10:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,6'4".\NEverybody is the victim
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.38,1:10:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of something.\NThe adjective now
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.59,1:10:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,describes the victim.\NThe refinement now is
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.60,1:10:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot mention a person's age.\NThere's a book out about it in fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.60,1:10:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A new book about it.\NThe truth police
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.60,1:11:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or something like that.\NAnyway, you can't mention age
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.60,1:11:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because somebody is going to feel victimized\Nand it's going to make them uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.92,1:11:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Victimization and being uncomfortable\Ngo hand in hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.18,1:11:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything makes you uncomfortable.\NYou can't mention gender.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.43,1:11:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't mention any physical data.\NYou can't mention any
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.43,1:11:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,data of any kind\Nbecause that might make people uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.77,1:11:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're bald, you're not bald.\NThat can make you uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.50,1:11:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't say a middle-aged bald man\Nbecause you would feel uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.50,1:11:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,if you called a middle-aged bald.\NThe gender police
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.56,1:11:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,would be after you.\NIt would be a middle-aged
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.75,1:11:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you were going to say a man or woman\Nbut you can't, person.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.75,1:11:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday on the news\Nwe talked about a waiting person.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.14,1:11:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It used to be a waitress.\NHonkers or hooters.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.46,1:12:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?\NNow you don't dare
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.46,1:12:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,refer to him as a waitress.\NIt was a wait person.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.82,1:12:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't have a gender\Nand you can't mention a gender.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.59,1:12:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a wait person.\NSo you see how
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.97,1:12:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,everything makes you uncomfortable\Nis the position of actually paranoia.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.69,1:12:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So what all this\Nreally leads to
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.69,1:12:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is the prevailing\Nparanoia of today's society
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.11,1:12:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you can't make a move.\NThe conversations back and forth
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.46,1:12:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with the hospital\Nand with the admitting doctor there
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.46,1:12:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,were endless.\NEvery one of them was a move
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.02,1:13:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,about whether we were\Ngoing with regulations,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.02,1:13:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,requirements,\Nwhether this was all being documented.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.06,1:13:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to keep carefully\Nthe time they called me,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.06,1:13:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the time they called me back.\NThen I called them back
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.06,1:13:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to say the doctor didn't call me back.\NHe called me to tell me
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.31,1:13:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he tried to call me back\Nbut the phone was busy.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.97,1:13:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to document that.\NHow does it sound in court?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.93,1:13:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Neglect.\NI couldn't get him,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.07,1:13:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,he couldn't get me.\NSomebody is going to be the victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.46,1:13:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the victim industry\Ndrives our economy right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.32,1:13:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Politically, war, politicians,\Neverybody is into the victim game.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.32,1:13:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the American public\Nthe victim of George?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.42,1:13:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,George's distortions\Nof reality?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.96,1:14:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they want to know.\NIs Saddam the victim
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.96,1:14:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of these horrible Americans?\NAre Americans the evil Satan?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.60,1:14:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they are, right?\NThey drive cars and we don't
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.85,1:14:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so we hate them.\NSomebody who is nobody
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.53,1:14:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in a nowhere country\Nstill living the Stone Age,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.53,1:14:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to go from nobody to somebody.\NTo go from nobody to somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.68,1:14:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the victim?\NHis innocence.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.93,1:14:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that the basic nature\Nof human nature,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.06,1:14:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that the mind intrinsically,\Nthe hardware of the mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.18,1:14:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself,\Nis unable to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.80,1:14:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that the programming coming in,\Nwhich we call the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.02,1:14:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is the software.\NWe know that because of the intrinsic
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.69,1:14:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,innocence of consciousness,\Nwe cannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.69,1:15:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, the Buddha,\NJesus, Krishna,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.69,1:15:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and every great teacher that ever lived\Nsaid, forgive them for they know
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.69,1:15:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,not what they do.\NThe one sin and the one sin only,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.69,1:15:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the Buddha said, is that of ignorance.\NHowever, don't you see that ignorance
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.11,1:15:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is inborn?\NYou're born with the incapacity
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.11,1:15:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to know truth from falsehood.\NThat is the most devastating fact
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.50,1:15:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of human history.\NMorally responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.72,1:15:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for every decision,\Nkarmically,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.56,1:15:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet\Nwith no compass
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.85,1:15:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to know what direction to go.\NThis throws mankind into
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.69,1:15:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,an extreme situation\Nwhere he can only hope
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.22,1:15:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that that which he's been taught\Nis somewhat near the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.22,1:15:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the likelihood is slim.\NThe likelihood is slim.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.93,1:16:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do what I usually do\Nis number two.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.93,1:16:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the wise then\Nwise up.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.51,1:16:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's\Nthe world's population again.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.40,1:16:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We're trying to get a different view\Nas spiritual students,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.40,1:16:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as devotees,\Nor whatever we want to designate ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.76,1:16:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the nature of the ego\Nand what is the nature of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.76,1:16:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's the relationship between\Nthe ego and how it sees and experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.76,1:16:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the world?\NHere we have a human population
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.36,1:16:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which over\Nhundreds of thousands of years
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.75,1:16:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,still can't even tell truth\Nfrom falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.32,1:16:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not even on the first rung\Nof the ladder,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.67,1:16:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,despite that profound ignorance.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.53,1:16:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,78% of the world\Nis still in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.53,1:17:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,78% of the world\Nhas not reached the level
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.53,1:17:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,where even to know truth from\Nfalsehood would be valued.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.53,1:17:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that phenomenal?\NPeople say, well, it isn't fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.01,1:17:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are suffering the\Nkarmic consequences of their ignorance
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.01,1:17:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and shouldn't we tell them\Nabout that, etc.?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.42,1:17:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you what, they're not interested.\NIf you go into the inner city
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.56,1:17:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and talk to the gang kids and tell them\Nthis way is integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.72,1:17:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and this way is not, they'll say,\Nyeah,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.73,1:17:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,good luck.\NGood luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.93,1:17:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But I gotta stay alive, if you don't mind.\NAnd if I don't join the gang
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.73,1:17:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and if I don't do what they do,\Nif I lose my rank
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.85,1:17:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or respect for me,\NI'm gonna get eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.38,1:17:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's very good to\Npontificate about
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.47,1:18:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,how they should be,\Nmoralize about it, idealize about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.23,1:18:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So we look at the evolution\Nof human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.93,1:18:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At the present time,\Nwe see that
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.00,1:18:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,only 20 some odd percent\Nis capable
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.15,1:18:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of discerning truth from falsehood\Nif they had a mechanism
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.15,1:18:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to do so.\NThe rest don't even care about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.82,1:18:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's put that previous one back on.\NWhat do the rest care about?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.31,1:18:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,People of integrity are excited.\NThey say, wow, there's a way of telling truth
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.31,1:18:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,from falsehood and even calibrating it?\NA lot of people get so excited
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.81,1:18:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,they can't eat for a week,\Nwhen I read that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.10,1:18:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo these are the mechanisms.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.38,1:18:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do the 78 percent live?\NWhere do they live?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.81,1:18:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They live because politicized,\Nmoralized and idealized,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.81,1:19:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,all these things create hate.\NThey create greed.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.39,1:19:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They create depression.\NThey create conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.88,1:19:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's where the lives are lived.\NIf you say to them,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.53,1:19:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we've got a way to discern\Nspiritual truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.56,1:19:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity from non-integrity,\Nand levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.56,1:19:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they try to figure out,\Nwell, where can we sell it?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.64,1:19:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Got a new product to move, folks.\NLet's move this new product, called
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.64,1:19:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the diggity.\NThat's the thing that's out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.60,1:19:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move this new product.\NWell, we should take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.32,1:20:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a tough morning.\NI thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.93,1:20:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd like to see the dog.\NCan we take his picture?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.93,1:20:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the dog,\Ncalibrates at 505.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.09,1:20:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And we saw this morning,\N78 percent of the population
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.09,1:20:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world is below 200.\NThe first characteristic,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.82,1:21:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I know another dog\Nthat calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.89,1:21:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was saying,\Nwhat is the difference?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.02,1:21:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another dog\Nthat calibrates also at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.06,1:21:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Its tail wags.\NIt just loves people.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.60,1:21:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wants something from you.\NIt comes up to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.69,1:21:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and it wants you to acknowledge it.\NYou notice this dog doesn't want anything from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.10,1:21:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that's the difference.\NIn order to get attention,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.61,1:21:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,he merely, if I look at him\Nand tell him he's a wonderful dog,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.61,1:21:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,he wags his tail.\NHe doesn't want anything from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.13,1:21:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not trying to control me.\NObviously, he doesn't care what we think about him.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.13,1:22:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see,\Nthe animal is,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.47,1:22:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he takes his joy from his own existence.\NAnd then the interactions
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.67,1:22:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,add to the joy.\NBut he doesn't need my attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.73,1:22:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, as many a dog,\Nhe will run up to you, he's wagging.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.98,1:22:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But he wants your attention.\NHe doesn't want anything from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.56,1:22:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He just ignores me.\NAnyway, I think you're a sweetheart,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.39,1:22:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and we thank you for coming up.\NThank you so much for letting us meet the dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.21,1:22:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So the joy comes from\None's own existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.39,1:22:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And without all\Nthe puzzling things going on
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.73,1:22:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,mentally that afflict humans,\Nhe's free to just
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.97,1:22:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,enjoy his own\Nexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.09,1:23:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the source of joy\Nas we become more and more enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.34,1:23:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That we begin to sense\Nthat the source of joy
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.63,1:23:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is our existence in this moment.\NIt's just this moment
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.63,1:23:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,right now.\NIt's sufficient unto itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.81,1:23:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So one gets outside\Nof the time dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.81,1:23:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because subjectivity\Ndoes not live within the dimension
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.81,1:23:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of time. It just\Nis.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.61,1:23:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So we remember Ramana Maharshi says,\Nthere's no point in trying
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.47,1:23:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to change the world, because the world\Nthat you see doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.47,1:23:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rejection\Nof your own perceptions.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.34,1:23:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no one to save.\NAnd people are always, we're affronted by that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.32,1:23:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they thought we should\Nbe doing something.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.32,1:23:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So all these illusory\Nmental states drive
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.32,1:24:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,people into doing things.\NDoing things about what they
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.32,1:24:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,imagine is wrong.\NIn a forest where a lot of the trees
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.27,1:24:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,have been killed off by the bark beetle,\Nwhat should you do with this
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.52,1:24:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,vast forest with these dead trees?\NSo some people say, well
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.35,1:24:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we must do something about it.\NThe fact that the tree's dead, we must cut it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.52,1:24:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to cut it down.\NIf it's a dead tree in the forest,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.55,1:24:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you leave it be. And in 20 or 30 years,\Nit just falls down.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.47,1:24:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to do anything.\NSo when people say that,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.09,1:24:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, how long do you suppose\Nthat forest has been there? 100,000 years or so?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.09,1:24:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody bothered\Ncutting down the dead trees
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.69,1:24:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,over 100,000 years.\NI guess we don't need to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.30,1:24:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So man is always interjecting himself\Nin nature and trying to improve
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.30,1:25:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,on that which does not need improvement.\NTo really see that,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.14,1:25:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,though, means to be totally\Naccepting, totally accepting.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.14,1:25:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, I thought we'd talk a little bit\Nabout the field
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.27,1:25:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the content of the field.\NAnd then I thought we'd do something
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.65,1:25:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we did someplace recently\Nwe talked.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.81,1:25:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of questions and answers coming up\Nby cards, although we do have cards,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.81,1:25:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,or a microphone traveling around\Nthe audience, we found that was not satisfactory,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.81,1:25:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we had people just come up\Nand we started discussing
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.89,1:25:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,things.\NI thought today we'll try that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.18,1:25:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to present a few things.\NAnd I thought people that want to talk
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.18,1:25:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to me, why don't you come up\Nand talk to me. We'll ask questions
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.18,1:25:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and discuss things as a small group,\Nbut the whole audience will hear the discussion.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.18,1:25:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that okay with you?\NBecause many people have questions,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.18,1:26:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't read\Nso well, so a 3x5 card,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.30,1:26:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,if somebody just tells me\Nwhat it is that's on their mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.77,1:26:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because an interview\Nis artificial. Somebody has written down
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.80,1:26:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,questions, but that's not really\Nwhat's bothering them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.80,1:26:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I like is the authenticity\Nof the one-to-one
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.02,1:26:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,people asking a question, because that is\Na real question to them. It's a real question,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.02,1:26:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,not something that was written down by an editor.\NAnd therefore they get a real answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.06,1:26:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So we did that\Nat Mile High. We didn't know that
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.11,1:26:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the microphone was on, see?\NAnd people were coming up with these questions,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.11,1:26:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course I'm just being my real self,\Nyou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.11,1:26:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She's\Nlamenting the illness of her daughter,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.11,1:26:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm telling her, well, you should go to a\N12-step group, you should go to Elman
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.11,1:26:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or something. She says, I've been going for 12 years.\NSo, because there was nobody witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.11,1:26:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,this, I thought, I said, well, for God's sake,\Nwhy don't you take the first step?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.11,1:27:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm shaking her, it's about time to take\Nthe first step after 12 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.11,1:27:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, she went into shock, you know.\NAnd so
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.14,1:27:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,my natural state is more like Zen\Nthan a Christian saint,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.14,1:27:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you know. And then after\Nthis is all over, all these people came up
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.22,1:27:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and we had, you know,\Na go-around with everybody, and the group was all
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.22,1:27:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,involved, and everybody was listening, you know.\NAnd then when it was over, we found
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.22,1:27:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the hall was full of people sitting there\Njust fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.22,1:27:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They were, you know, right in the middle of\Nthese conversations, and we didn't even know
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.22,1:27:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,this was on, you know.\NBut then I thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.10,1:27:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, maybe that's a good thing to do.\NWe haven't tried it with this audience, so maybe we should
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.10,1:27:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,do that.\NAll right, so first I'll explain
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.10,1:27:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a few other things I always want to clarify,\Nand then I thought, well, people
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.47,1:27:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,will ask us real questions. We'll start\Nwith the ones that we...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.02,1:28:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh, real good one, uh-oh.\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.06,1:28:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Betty prompted me, said,\Nyou mentioned the 12-step program.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.06,1:28:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people are not familiar with it?\NOkay, so there's more than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.68,1:28:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so prevalent in our society\Nthat almost everybody has a relative,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.68,1:28:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a friend, a fellow employee,\Ntheir boss, or somebody,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.71,1:28:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the 12-step idea,\Nyou know, came out of
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.28,1:28:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the Oxford Groups.\NThe Oxford Groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.35,1:28:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And, um,\Nthe Oxford Groups lived by
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.40,1:28:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain set of spiritual principles.\NIt was just a spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.50,1:28:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,pathway.\NIt consisted of
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.76,1:28:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the Oxford principles,\NI think there was only six, not 12,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.76,1:28:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and it had nothing to do with alcoholism.\NBut when Roland, who was
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.07,1:28:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a hopeless alcoholic,\Nwent to see Carl Jung in Switzerland,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.52,1:29:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung was, of course,\Na very great and famous psychoanalyst.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.52,1:29:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And after seeing Jung\Nfor some time, he moved to Switzerland
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.75,1:29:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to be in psychoanalysis\Nwith Jung.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.48,1:29:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And he became sober.\NSo Roland went back to New York City
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.48,1:29:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and within a short time\Nwas drunk again.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.55,1:29:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And so Roland went back\Nto Switzerland
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.81,1:29:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to see Carl Jung.\NWhat should I do now?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.81,1:29:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,His great hope was Carl Jung\Nand his psychoanalysis,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.06,1:29:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and now he had collapsed again.\NSo in the depths of depression,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.06,1:29:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,he pleaded with Carl Jung.\NCarl Jung, to whom we are all grateful
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.31,1:29:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to this day,\Nhe calibrated 520.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.60,1:29:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Carl Jung said,\Nhe was honest, he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.11,1:29:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,alas, alas, he said,\Nneither my science nor my art
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.34,1:29:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,can help you.\NHowever, it has been recorded,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.81,1:29:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,rarely, but it has been recorded\Nby people who have recovered
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.81,1:30:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,by throwing themselves wholeheartedly\Ninto a spiritual group.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.18,1:30:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So Roland went back to the United States\Nvery dejected and very depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.18,1:30:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I guess he was\Nnot a very spiritual person.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.36,1:30:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, he threw himself in\Nwholeheartedly into the Oxford groups
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.36,1:30:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and lo and behold, Roland became sober.\NRoland passed this on to
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.35,1:30:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Evie, who came to Bill W.\NAnd Bill W
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.39,1:30:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,was in the same state of despair\Nand they told him
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.42,1:30:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that only by turning himself over to God\Ncould he have any chance of hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.42,1:30:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Bill was an atheist\Nat the time, so it didn't
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.42,1:30:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,appeal to him too much.\NBut also, at death's door,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.46,1:30:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill W did surrender\Nall of the ego to God
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.46,1:30:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and the room lit up\Nwith a great light.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.97,1:31:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And he went through\Na profound transformation
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.59,1:31:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which arose all the 12 step\Nrecovery groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.90,1:31:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of that one moment,\Nthe room lit up.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.90,1:31:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that, millions\Nof people have recovered
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.90,1:31:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from all kinds of diseases\Nby following these 12 basic steps.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.06,1:31:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The first demonstration\Nof this efficacy
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.57,1:31:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was in the curing of alcoholism,\Nwhich many people here don't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.57,1:31:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because in the modern era\Nit's considered to be recoverable.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.57,1:31:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In the old days, it was a sentence of death.\NNobody recovered.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.71,1:31:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You died of a wet brain\Nbecause of insanity and convulsions.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.64,1:31:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So here was witnessed\Nby everybody around
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.80,1:31:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the miraculous recovery\Nfrom a hopeless progressive disease.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.80,1:31:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So the word spread\Nand AA grew
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.43,1:31:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course it now is worldwide.\NWell, if these 12 steps
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.43,1:32:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,could bring about recovery\Nfrom hopeless progressive diseases
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.43,1:32:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,for which there was no cure\Nbecause medicine, psychiatry
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.43,1:32:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and psychology have no cure for it\Nand neither does religion,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.43,1:32:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Catholic priests\Nwho have an alcoholism rate
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.76,1:32:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of 10 or 15 percent\Nto get sober and go to AA.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.76,1:32:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So there was something about\Nthe 12 steps then
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.07,1:32:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,had great power.\NPeople began to apply this
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.23,1:32:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to other illnesses\Nand so now the 12 step recovery
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.23,1:32:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,principles\Nwhich calibrated 540
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.27,1:32:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are applied\Nto many of life's intractable problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.36,1:32:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Drug addiction,\Nalcoholism,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.17,1:32:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,drug addiction and loss\Nand people who are prone to violence
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.17,1:32:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and anger and rage\Nand all kinds of victimhood
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.19,1:32:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and spending people\Nare compulsive spenders etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.19,1:32:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of things\Nfor which there really is no cure
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.42,1:33:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,hopeless illnesses.\NSo it was found then
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.42,1:33:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that the energy fuel\Nthat calibrates at 540
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.42,1:33:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,had the capacity\Nif you did the steps,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.64,1:33:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore I have a great interest in it\Naside from alcoholism
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.64,1:33:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,just the 12 steps themselves\Nmuch as I have an interest
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.86,1:33:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the course of miracles\Nwhich calibrates at 600
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.86,1:33:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the course of which\NI've seen recovery from
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.89,1:33:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,endless numbers\Nof hopeless diseases
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.06,1:33:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from multiple sclerosis\Nto myasthenia gravis
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.15,1:33:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to all kinds of incurables.\NSo we know that spiritual power
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.15,1:33:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,then has the capacity\Nwhen it's karmically okay to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.15,1:33:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman called me\NI'd seen and she said
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.51,1:33:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\NI went through a spiritual transformation
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.98,1:33:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and she said\Nthe cancer of the breast had disappeared
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.18,1:34:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,she called me up to tell me\Nthe x-ray showed
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.18,1:34:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it was now gone.\NRather everyday occurrences
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.34,1:34:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,within the power of the spiritual field\Nanything may recover
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.34,1:34:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you do\Nthe 12 steps
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.35,1:34:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,or you do the course of miracles\Nthoroughly
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.46,1:34:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't matter whether you recover or not\Nbecause recovery
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.46,1:34:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is trying to control God\Nonce you surrender to God
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.46,1:34:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,if this is the way you're going to go\Nthen this is the way you're going to go
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.21,1:34:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so let's look at the 12 steps\Nfor those who are not familiar with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.06,1:34:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I recommend the 12 steps\Nto anybody in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.06,1:34:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for anything\Nbecause it is merely
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.64,1:34:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual way of living.\NThe Oxford groups
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.86,1:34:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the Oxford groups were not religious\Nthey said what is the spiritual core
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.86,1:34:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the spiritual core of truth\Nbecause they were disillusioned
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.97,1:35:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with traditional religion.\NThe first one
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.02,1:35:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we admit we are powerless\Nand in our case
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.02,1:35:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as seekers of enlightenment over the ego\Nand that our lives have become unmanageable
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.02,1:35:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and you say\Nmy life is unmanageable
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.56,1:35:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,my life is not unmanageable\Nand I say well let's see
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.56,1:35:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,let's stop your mind\Nfrom thinking for a second
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.56,1:35:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't think it was unmanageable\Nyou just learned in one second
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.56,1:35:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that it goes right on\Nit thumbs its nose at you
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.72,1:35:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind and your ego\Nthumb their nose at you
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.10,1:35:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell it not to do this\Nand it will promptly do that
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.10,1:35:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,do not forget to put the butter\Nback in the refrigerator
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.10,1:35:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you get home from the movie\Nand the cat's been licking it
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.10,1:35:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,while you were gone.\Nand you want to
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.10,1:35:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,change the world\Nthey want to change
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.30,1:36:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,all these people want to change the world\Ncan't remember to tie their shoelaces
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.02,1:36:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,ok so first is the surrender of humility\Nso the secret of success
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.02,1:36:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of the course of miracles\Nor this spiritual pathway
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.02,1:36:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,or devotional non-duality\Nis humility
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.05,1:36:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize the profound limitation\Nof the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.07,1:36:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the great difficulty\Nthe slightest thing
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.88,1:36:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore when we looked at ourselves\Nhonestly
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.88,1:36:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so the first step is one of honesty\Npeople that are in hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.30,1:36:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and down below 200\Nstep one takes you to
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.86,1:36:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity right away\Nstep one you're honest with yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.34,1:36:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,left to my own devices\Nthere's really nothing I can do about this
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.34,1:36:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,condition therefore\Nthrough experience
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.65,1:36:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't say through experience\Nbut it says came to believe
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.65,1:37:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that a power greater than ourselves\Ncould restore us to sanity
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.90,1:37:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,sanity doesn't mean lying in bed\Nworrying about everything
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.38,1:37:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean trying to anticipate\Ntomorrow's disasters
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.38,1:37:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't mean ruminating\Nabout the wrongs of the past
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.38,1:37:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it means\Npeople don't know what sanity is
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.23,1:37:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind itself is silent\Nstill
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.61,1:37:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it says nothing\Nit doesn't say anything to you
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.53,1:37:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to think God is talking to you\Nsomething is talking to you
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.68,1:37:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,space doesn't talk to you\Nbut in space
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.06,1:37:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a knowingness begins to arise\Nit arises
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.06,1:37:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the outer fields of consciousness\Nthrough the knowing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.06,1:38:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a knowingness of the field\Nit comes about through the knowingness of the field
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.06,1:38:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,if God spoke to you\Nit would turn you into a cinder
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.47,1:38:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in a second\Nif an archangel even hears a prayer
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.02,1:38:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and passes a thought to you\Nit would blow you out for 30 years
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.73,1:38:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,stunned into silence\Nthe mind never speaks again
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.73,1:38:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and if God thought of you\Nholy catfish
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.61,1:38:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,came to believe that a power greater than ourselves\Ncould restore us to sanity
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.93,1:38:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,step three\Nwe made a decision to turn our will
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.93,1:38:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and our lives over to the care of God\Nas we understood them
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.22,1:38:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,turn our will\Nand our lives over to God
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.81,1:38:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see\Nthe power of the crux of this
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.14,1:38:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is the profound humility\Nit means no matter what
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.43,1:39:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the no matter whatness\Narises again just as you break through
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.93,1:39:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,into the state of enlightenment\Nno matter what
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.73,1:39:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,one gets at the last door\Nthat one
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.06,1:39:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is expected or needs to\Nor the field
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.44,1:39:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,lets you know\Nthat at this point you turn your life
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.80,1:39:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,itself over to God\Nand you surrender your life
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.31,1:39:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you think is your life\Nyou believe that all these lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.31,1:39:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,all these hundreds of thousands of lifetimes\Nyou think this is the me
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.23,1:39:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of life\Nyou think the ego is you
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.52,1:39:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is the source of your life\Nand now you're expected to surrender that
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.52,1:39:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,having surrendered everything else\Nthat's all that's left
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.68,1:39:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,without profound humility\Nyou wouldn't have the courage
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.10,1:39:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to make the last step\Nmade a decision to turn our will
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.30,1:40:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and our lives\Nlife itself over to God
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.30,1:40:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as we understand him\Nin that moment
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.93,1:40:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as I've said before\Nthe Zen teaching to walk straight ahead
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.93,1:40:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what\Nthe faith of the vibrational field
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.53,1:40:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of the guru came back\Nand I knew I could
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.72,1:40:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,place even my life\Nin the truth of that saying
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.05,1:40:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and so a teacher should prepare you\Nfor what is going to arise
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.23,1:40:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,made a decision to turn our will\Nand our very life
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.23,1:40:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,our very life itself\Nin the case of enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.61,1:40:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,over to God as you understood\Nand at that point
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.61,1:40:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the unknown\Nto turn over that which you believe
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.22,1:40:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,most profoundly and most intrinsically\Nis the source and essence of your life
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.22,1:40:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to the unknown\Nrequires great faith and humility
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.89,1:40:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,step four\Nthe steps are practical
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.35,1:41:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,made a searching and fearless\Nmoral inventory of ourselves
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.98,1:41:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't say of other people\Nlaughter
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.38,1:41:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter\Nmade it for
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.60,1:41:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we looked within ourselves\Nso we became
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.60,1:41:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we began to witness the mind\Nwe followed Nisargadatta Maharaj's
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.60,1:41:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,instruction watch the mind\Nbegin to look at the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.60,1:41:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,this is what we did this morning\Nwe said 98% of the mind is silent
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.60,1:41:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only 2% that's giving you a problem\Nwhat about that 2%
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.27,1:41:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so we made a searching and fearless\Nmoral inventory of ourselves
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.26,1:41:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,two people with more advanced consciousness\Npeople seeking enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.26,1:41:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is not just rights and wrongs\Nand goods and bads
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.10,1:41:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,once we are aware of certain knowledge\Nnow we feel sort of morally
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.10,1:41:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,obligated to\Nsee it through to its conclusion
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.10,1:41:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,once you can see the mind\Nis prone to criticizing
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.18,1:42:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and fatalizing idealizing\Nglamorizing
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.11,1:42:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,etc now one feels\Ncalled upon to call it at
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.11,1:42:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that and see how it's doing it\Nbecause as you do
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.11,1:42:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the underlying motive will arise\Nreveal the underlying motive
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.27,1:42:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so we became\Nmorally integrous
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.27,1:42:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so it says we became morally integrous\Nso you can see every step takes you above 200
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.27,1:42:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's impossible to do the 12 steps\Nand still be below 200
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.27,1:42:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not possible\Nnobody can do the
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.92,1:42:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual steps and still calibrate below 200\Nit's not possible
Dialogue: 0,1:42:36.34,1:42:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the 12 steps themselves\Nas I mentioned
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.34,1:42:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 540\Nwhich is the energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.34,1:42:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and healing itself\Nso we admitted to
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.26,1:42:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,God to ourselves\Nand to another human being
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.26,1:42:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the exact nature\Nof what we call wrongs and quotes
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.73,1:43:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to more advanced\Npeople a wrong would be like
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.94,1:43:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectualizing you know\Nto people down here it would be stealing from the boss
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.94,1:43:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or killing your neighbor's cat\Nmaybe
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.30,1:43:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the exact nature of our wrongs\Nnow
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.59,1:43:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,people resist\Nstep four
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.46,1:43:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they say well if I do step four\NI'm going to go into a guilt bag
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.46,1:43:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and people\Ndo step four on paper
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.97,1:43:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they write down all the nature\Nof all their wrongs
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.35,1:43:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they say I'm going to get into a guilt trip\Nand they're scared of it
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.35,1:43:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so step five is the resolution\Nof that guilt trip
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.35,1:43:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you share\Nyour list of horrors
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.38,1:43:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with another human being\Nwho is spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.38,1:43:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and you respect\Nand because you want to have
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.73,1:43:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all secrets\Nwill destroy you
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.93,1:44:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a moral secret that you've never shared with anybody\Neats away at you
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.93,1:44:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,eats away at you\Nno matter how
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.81,1:44:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what\Nwe find someone
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.92,1:44:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you think this is a good person\Nto be with
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.14,1:44:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you can check it out with kinesiology\Nyes this is a good person I can be with
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.14,1:44:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody who is spiritual\Nintegrity
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.52,1:44:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you respect\Nso you admit to God
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.77,1:44:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to yourself and to another human being\Nso step five is where some people
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.77,1:44:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,weasel out\Nfour in five
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.39,1:44:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,shakes the sheep from the goats\Nwinnows out the shaft
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.85,1:44:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you really want to go\Nthe whole way then you wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.85,1:44:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,let fear and guilt about sharing who you are\Nwith somebody else stand in your way
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.05,1:44:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and so then you're forced to\Nconfront spiritual pride
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.05,1:45:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,your fear\Nwhat people think about you
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.56,1:45:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,how you project your self\Nassessment onto others and then expect
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.56,1:45:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to see you the same way you're seeing yourself\Nand this is certainly
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.90,1:45:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,putting faith and trust in another human being\Nthis is of course traditional
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.47,1:45:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in many spiritual pathways\Nthe Catholic has their
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.47,1:45:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,confessor and AA\None has a sponsor
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.85,1:45:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's traditional then\Ninstead of walking around with your
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.85,1:45:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,hidden horrible little secrets clutched to your\Nbosom
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.60,1:45:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that you share them with somebody\Nand I've heard everything
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.89,1:45:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you can hear on this planet\Nso you could have a good doctor
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.89,1:45:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you could have a good psychiatrist\Nyou could certainly have a good priest
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.19,1:45:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you could have a confessor\Nand one hears everything there is to hear
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.52,1:45:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know after hearing all of it\Nall those years
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.02,1:46:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,when I think about it\Nit's a so what
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.18,1:46:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I ran over five kids\Nand they all fell down
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.18,1:46:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I killed my mother-in-law\Nand robbed the bank
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.38,1:46:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and cut her throat\Nand I said yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.53,1:46:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's bothering you now\Nwhy
Dialogue: 0,1:46:16.85,1:46:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's the way it was at that time\Nwhat that person was at that time
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.89,1:46:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what that person did at that time\Nbecause each one is being what they can
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.89,1:46:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,only being what they can be at the time\Nif you're run by a criminal mind
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.76,1:46:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then you do criminal things\Nand now when you've given
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.76,1:46:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,up being a criminal\Nit looks horrible to you
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.07,1:46:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but you weren't the person you are now\Nat that time
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.07,1:46:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so at that time\Neverybody did what they could do
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.14,1:46:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing better and nothing worse\Nif you could have been more honest
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.14,1:46:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have been\Nyou didn't have the moral fortitude
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.36,1:46:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't have the support\Nnow you've got support
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.39,1:47:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the karmic benefit\Nof inner and outer honesty
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.10,1:47:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you're willing to change\Nso there's a profound benefit
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.10,1:47:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in doing five\Nand once you go after five
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.10,1:47:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you can breathe easy\Nfour and five is the tough one
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.84,1:47:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,step six is another one\Nof surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.77,1:47:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we're entirely ready\Nto have God remove
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.77,1:47:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all these defects of character\Nhave God remove these
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.53,1:47:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so we surrender them to God\Nso all the things we did on the list
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.53,1:47:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,this morning\Ndear God I really need help
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.53,1:47:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,criticalness\Nmy constantly politicizing everything
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.81,1:47:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,idealizing everything\Nmoralizing about everything
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.81,1:47:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,can't anything happen in this world\Nwithout my having an opinion on it
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.89,1:47:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,do I have to keep hating chocolate\Nor can I just let chocolate
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.89,1:48:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,be chocolate and say\NI prefer vanilla
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.02,1:48:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,ok so if politics\Nwas cheering on your favorite
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.02,1:48:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,championing a belief system\Nit would be great but it tends to take on
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.02,1:48:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,attacking chocolate\Nalright
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.02,1:48:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,continue to take personal inventory\Nwe asked him
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.22,1:48:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to remove our shortcomings\Nso you see that's the essence of it
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.22,1:48:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,now one could use\Na mechanism you ask God to remove
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.22,1:48:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,your shortcomings\Nand the next thing your mother says to you
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.42,1:48:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is maybe you ought to see\Na psychiatrist
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.69,1:48:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how God wants you to remove\Nthat shortcoming
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.69,1:48:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so the mechanism here the psychiatrist\Nhe's only the mechanism
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.53,1:48:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,when you ask God for help\Nwith something and a guy
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.65,1:48:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,screeches up to you and says\Nyou got a flat tire can I help
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.65,1:48:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean that isn't God but\NI've had it happen in the middle of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.65,1:48:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,completely deserted\Nand a guy pulls up next to me
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.92,1:49:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he says you got problems\Nthe tire is flat
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.07,1:49:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he puts it on his truck\Nhe drives it into his town
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.59,1:49:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,gets it fixed brings it back to me\Nand helps me put it on
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.46,1:49:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,humbly ask God to remove our shortcomings\Nand God may suggest a mechanism
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.46,1:49:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you need Prozac\Nwell of course
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.18,1:49:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the miracle says physical mental and spiritual\Nand AA and the 12 step group
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.18,1:49:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,say physical mental and spiritual\Nif you really want to stop being depressed
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.18,1:49:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,then you wouldn't be resistant\Nabout taking an antidepressant
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.18,1:49:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,if you really wanted to be undepressed\Nthen you would take an antidepressant wouldn't you
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.18,1:49:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the very fact that you don't want to take it\Nmeans that you're getting juice out of being depressed
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.18,1:49:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,getting to be the sick victim\Nand the old poor me
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.34,1:49:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,okay so resistance\Nso each step brings up resistance
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.38,1:49:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,next to undo the guilt\Nwe made a list of all the persons we harmed
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.38,1:49:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and became willing to make amends to them all\Nit doesn't say in that step that you do
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.81,1:50:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't say you write your boss yeah\Nit says you became willing
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.75,1:50:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so willingness\Nwillingness on our calibrated chart
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.75,1:50:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the high 300's\Nso you see
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.88,1:50:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as you do the steps it's automatically\Ngoing to take you up the calibrated scale of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.88,1:50:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,into humility\Ninto willingness
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.93,1:50:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so we became willing\Nto make amends to them all
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.93,1:50:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then where possible\Nwe made direct amends whenever possible
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.32,1:50:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,except when\Nto do them would create scandal
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.32,1:50:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,injure them\Nor others
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.22,1:50:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there's some things that to reveal it\Nwould be so disturbing to people
Dialogue: 0,1:50:44.22,1:50:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that out of compassion for them\Nthen out of compassion
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.22,1:50:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for them\Nso this is another reason to have a counselor
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.35,1:50:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or a confessor\Nor a priest or a doctor
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.93,1:51:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatrist psychologist therapist\Ngood friend
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.72,1:51:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,one's parents can sometimes\Nunder unusual circumstances
Dialogue: 0,1:51:05.72,1:51:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,even one's spouse\Nyou can admit to a spouse
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.81,1:51:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I did such and such\Nand I sure wish I hadn't
Dialogue: 0,1:51:13.81,1:51:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and if there's real love there\Nso a true relationship
Dialogue: 0,1:51:17.81,1:51:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're aligned\Nwith one as therapeutically
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.81,1:51:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and loving as possible\Nso people who have a good relationship
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.81,1:51:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or a good marriage relationship\Nor a very good friend
Dialogue: 0,1:51:29.92,1:51:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you can reveal almost anything\Nand they will try to recontextualize it
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.92,1:51:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see it differently\Nspiritual work is considerably
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.10,1:51:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,as you know by now\Nrecontextualizing a thing
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.10,1:51:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so what you thought was the worst thing in the world\Nwhen recontextualized
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.30,1:51:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize is due to the weakness of human nature\Nincluding your own
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.50,1:51:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the weakness of human nature\Nand the limitation of human nature
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.61,1:51:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is what accounts for most of the things\Nwe shake our heads over
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.64,1:52:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so we tried to make amends to people\Nwhen we could
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.64,1:52:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,except when to do so\Nwould injure them or others
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.44,1:52:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so that precludes dumping\Nbecause you feel guilty about
Dialogue: 0,1:52:12.44,1:52:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the affair you had 32 years ago\Nyou don't have to blow your wife away now
Dialogue: 0,1:52:16.44,1:52:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell her about that night\Nyou got drunk in Chicago
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.18,1:52:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean you wish it hadn't happened\Nagonizing you for 32 years with guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.18,1:52:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but to dump it on her\Nis dumping
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.88,1:52:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's misusing her\Nit's going to hurt her
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.88,1:52:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and it doesn't really mean anything\Nit's better to discuss
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.19,1:52:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with a confessor\Nshould I bring this up
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.19,1:52:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what's your purpose\Njust so you don't feel so guilty
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.19,1:52:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,well good for you but what about her\Nso you have to look at the consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.19,1:52:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and avoid\Ndumping your stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.19,1:53:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,on others\Nwe made direct amends
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.10,1:53:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,then step 10 is what\Nmakes this different from many others
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.10,1:53:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we continue to take personal inventory\Non a daily basis
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.10,1:53:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we were wrong\Npromptly admitted it
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.98,1:53:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,just think of poor old Nixon\Nthinks a lot of people
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.98,1:53:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that have gone down the tubes\Nthat if they told the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.27,1:53:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and admitted it right at the beginning\Neverybody said well I was pretty dumb
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.27,1:53:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but so\Npromptly admitted it
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.10,1:53:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so we don't have to walk around\Nwith guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.35,1:53:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because when we were wrong\Nwe promptly admitted
Dialogue: 0,1:53:40.13,1:53:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and couples do that all the time\NI'm sorry I snapped at you
Dialogue: 0,1:53:44.13,1:53:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I forgot to bring home the butter\NI'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.38,1:53:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,people apologize for\Ncharacter logic problems
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.09,1:53:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's consideration of others\Nwe continue to take personal inventory
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.31,1:54:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we were wrong\Npromptly admitted it
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.34,1:54:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,just think of poor old Nixon\Nthinks a lot of people
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.34,1:54:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that have gone down the tubes\Ntend to eğ
Dialogue: 0,1:54:30.07,1:54:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,thing would have blown away and everybody would have forgiven them so we\Nfind that in the long term to admit when you're wrong right off the bat is
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.85,1:54:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,actually the best way to go the most practical and certainly politics has\Nproven that over and over again hiding a thing away and sooner or later comes out
Dialogue: 0,1:54:52.81,1:55:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and now and now the cost is great can cost you the the office itself and you\Nhave to resign so instead of a slap on the wrist you have a major catastrophe
Dialogue: 0,1:55:06.07,1:55:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's very practical step 10 also you can stay in integrity step 11 is the\Nbackbone of many a person's spiritual work sought through prayer and meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:55:21.90,1:55:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to become more conscious we all move towards enlightenment conscious contact\Nwith God as we understood him praying only for his knowledge of his will for
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.00,1:55:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,us\Noh that's different then please God do this and please God do that that's the
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.72,1:55:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,child in us running for the bus with your violin you're gonna be late for\Nyour violin lesson and you're praying up a storm God please hold the bus I can
Dialogue: 0,1:55:59.46,1:56:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,remember that the violin flying through the air and running like a mad dog less\Nschool late and now it's gonna miss the bus and miss my violin listen dear God
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.93,1:56:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,please hold the bus yeah\Nso in this we surrender our will to God and we ask for knowledge of his will for
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.82,1:56:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,us so you're asking for spiritual intuition a certain knowingness so\Nyou're trying to transcend the ego the ego lives in this box and the ego says
Dialogue: 0,1:56:31.47,1:56:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,well I'll figure it out but surrendering it to God is not figuring it out it's\Nnot figuring it out at all in fact it may look quite hopeless and a
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.71,1:56:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but we continue in humility.\NWe seek through prayer and meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:47.77,1:56:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And what then happens is it suddenly comes to us\Na recontextualization of what we thought was a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.35,1:57:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we see it wasn't even a problem in the first place.\NAnd if you'd gotten that job, you would have gone down
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.06,1:57:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because you didn't know what that company was\Nin its last few months.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.03,1:57:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And so step 11 then, prayer and meditation.\NAnd step 12 is one reason many of us are here.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:18.27,1:57:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Having had a spiritual awakening\Nas a result of a spiritually integrous life,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.47,1:57:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we tried to carry this message to others\Nand practice these principles in all our affairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.65,1:57:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So we then began to uplift others\Nby sharing our experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.78,1:57:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, sharing your experience\Nis not trying to change the other person.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:43.47,1:57:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll tell this person this for their own good.\NDon't do anything for anybody's own good.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:50.46,1:57:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, say, I went to Course in Miracles\Nand I saw people recover from myasthenia gravis,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:57.59,1:58:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,cancer, tumors, convulsive disorder.\NAnd you leave off, and therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.63,1:58:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you ought to be going.
